 Evaluation, AUGUST 2011 by S. F. Mughabghab (BNL)                9446 1451
                                                                  9446 1451
A new evaluation for the thermal, resonance and unresolved        9446 1451
resonance regions, as well as fast capture cross section          9446 1451
is carried out for version ENDF/B.VII.1. The motivation is the    9446 1451
results of the analysis of Palmiotti and Hiruta [Pu11],           9446 1451
where a 12.2 % discrepancy was observed between measured          9446 1451
and calculated capture reaction rates for Am-243, when the        9446 1451
JENDL-4 was used in the calculations.                             9446 1451
A detailed analysis and careful examination of measured           9446 1451
and evaluated capture cross sections of JENDL-4 in the thermal,   9446 1451
resonance and unresolved energy regions revealed that the major   9446 1451
source of the discrepancy is produced by                          9446 1451
the fast capture cross section which was calculated in JENDL-4    9446 1451
by a nuclear model in the energy region 45-800 keV.               9446 1451
                                                                  9446 1451
 Based on recent thermal capture cross section measurements of    9446 1451
Marie et al. [Ma06],  Bendt and Jurney [Be79],                    9446 1451
as well as an earlier pile neutron  cross section                 9446 1451
measurement of  Butler et al. [Bu56]( corrected for the presently 9446 1451
evaluated resonance integral), an evaluated 2200 m/s capture      9446 1451
cross section of 21.28-+0.77 b is derived  in the present         9446 1451
analysis. This is to be compared with an ENDF/B.VII.0 and an      9446 1451
Atlas [Mu06] values of  19.2 b  and 18.5-+0.5 b, respectively.    9446 1451
